# Golden Rule — English-Only Code

**All code identifiers, file names, directory names, URL paths, and comments must be written in English. No exceptions.**

## What must be in English

| Element | Examples |
|---|---|
| Function / method names | `getPatient`, `createAppointment`, `handleSearch` |
| Variable names | `firstName`, `appointmentDate`, `isLoading` |
| Struct / type / interface names | `DailyActivityReport`, `CreateInput`, `PatientRepository` |
| File names | `appointment_repository.go`, `SpecialistManagementReport.tsx` |
| Directory names | `ReferralTab/`, `Keratometry/`, `Diagnosis/` |
| URL route paths | `/bulk-import/scheduled-appointments`, `/admin/patients` |
| API endpoint segments | `/scheduled-appointments` not `/consultas-agendadas` |
| Code comments | `// Returns the best available discount for the lens` |
| Go package names | `package appointment`, `package bulkimport` |
| React component names | `ProsthesisTab`, `EvolutionsTab`, `ManagementReportBulkUpload` |
| Custom hook names | `usePatients`, `useAppointments` |
| Constant names | `SCHEDULED_APPOINTMENTS_CONFIG`, `ImportTypePatients` |
| CSS class names (custom) | `.patient-card`, `.modal-overlay` |

## What MUST stay in Spanish (UI content)

These are user-facing strings — they must stay in Spanish:

- Text labels, placeholders, button labels visible to the user
- Toast messages and error messages shown in the UI
- Page titles and navigation labels
- Validation messages returned by the API as HTTP response bodies
- Excel column header strings used in bulk-import templates (data contract)

```tsx
// CORRECT — UI text in Spanish, identifiers in English
const handleSearch = () => { ... }
<button onClick={handleSearch}>Buscar paciente</button>
toast({ title: 'Paciente creado', description: 'El paciente fue registrado.' })

// WRONG — identifier in Spanish
const handleBuscar = () => { ... }
```

## JSON tags / API contracts

Existing JSON tags (`json:"preguntas_hombre"`) and API field names that are part of an active frontend↔backend contract **must not be changed unilaterally**. The Go struct field name must be in English but the tag stays as-is until a planned migration.

```go
// CORRECT — field name in English, json tag preserves existing contract
InquiriesMale int `json:"preguntas_hombre" gorm:"not null;default:0"`

// WRONG — field name in Spanish
PreguntasHombre int `json:"preguntas_hombre"`
```

## Enforcement checklist before committing

- [ ] No Spanish words in any function, variable, struct, or file name
- [ ] No Spanish words in URL path segments (`/api/v1/...`)
- [ ] No Spanish comments in any `.go`, `.ts`, or `.tsx` file
- [ ] UI strings visible to the user are still in Spanish
- [ ] New files follow English naming: `feature_name.go`, `FeatureName.tsx`
